README
/////////////////////////////////////
DEATH TRAP CAR RACING
/////////////////////////////////////

Credits:
This game is created by Clinton Tong and Daniel Wei
Base on a modified open source graphic engine SPARKY(early version)
which can be found at  https://github.com/TheCherno/Sparky
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Introduction:
This project is divided into two parts
The first part is the game engine, it includes a graphic engine and a sound engine.
The translation of java to openGL is handled by a light weight open source library 
LWJGL library, the sound engine is powered by openAL. 
The second part is the game level.
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Check Lists:
PACKAGE CAR: MAIN.JAVA
PACKAGE AUDIO:LWJGLEXCEPTION.JAVA; MASTERAUDIO.JAVA; SOURCE.JAVA; WAVEDATA.JAVA; TRAFFIC.WAV;CRASH.WAV
PACKAGE GRAPHICS: SHADER.JAVA;  TEXTURE.JAVA; VERTEXARRAY.JAVA
PACKAGE INPUT: INPUT.JAVA
PACKAGE LEVEL: BLOCK.JAVA; LEVEL.JAVA; PLAYER.JAVA
PACKAGE MATHS: MATRIX4F.JAVA; VECTOR3F.JAVA
PACKAGE UTILS: BUFFERUTILS.JAVA; FILEUTILS.JAVA; SHADERUTILS.JAVA
RES FOLDER: CAR.PNG; BLOCK.PNG; BG.PNG
SHADERS FOLDER
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

TO RUN:

1. Download LWJGL version 3.0 from https://www.lwjgl.org/download
2. Check slick-util.jar is inside source folder
3. If not, download slick-util.jar from http://slick.ninjacave.com/slick-util/
3. Make sure you are running JavaSE 1.5 - 1.7(1.8 WILL NOT RUN)
4. Delete existing java build path from Library tab
5. Add external LWJGL jar file
6. Set native to LWJGL native path
7. Add external slick-util jar file
8. OK to run

